<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430725>
    dc:description "FIGURES 26–37. (26–29). Maladera cardoni (Brenske, 1896) (Purba bardhaman, west Bengal); (30–33). Maladera drescheri (Moser, 1913) (Jalpaiguri, West Bengal); (34–37). Maladera freyi Ahrens & Fabrizi, 2016 (West Champaran, Bihar); (26, 30, 34) Aedeagus in lateral view (left); (27, 31, 35) Aedeagus in dorsal view; (28, 32, 36) Aedeagus in lateral view (right); (29, 33, 37) Habitus, dorsal view. Scale 0.5 mm. Habitus not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430725/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430745>
    dc:description "FIGURE 98. (A–B). A. Gangetic plains biogeographic zone of India; B. Map of Lower Gangetic plains showing sample localities of the species: Maladera kolkataensis, Gynaecoserica perdita, Maladera affinis, M. allopruinosa, M. bengalensi, M. burmeisteri burmeisteri, M. cardoni." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430745/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

